The paper involves the use of neural network predictors and natural language processing to predict the duration of power outages. This suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of natural language processing indicates that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of power outages, which could be considered a security issue, making it a possible fit for the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
